{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54797d08-0f9b-42fa-903e-b2ae16cb9300","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. Your project targets:\n\n| TFM | MSTest v3 Support |\n|-----|-------------------|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for modern .NET targets. Both `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are out of support and no longer compatible.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or later (e.g., `net8.0`).\n2. Update the package references — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` packages.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ae49c30-23a3-4857-8b08-2912da289ef4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nLet me think about compatibility issues:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 drops support for older frameworks**. MSTest v3 requires at minimum:\n   - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/modern .NET)\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2+ \n\n   Wait, let me think more carefully:\n   - `net5.0` — .NET 5 is out of support, and MSTest v3 dropped support for it. MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0+.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — .NET Core 3.1 is also out of support and not supported by MSTest v3.\n   - `net462` — .NET Framework 4.6.2 should still be supported by MSTest v3.\n\n2. **MSTest v3 consolidates packages** — Instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`, you can use the single `MSTest` meta-package (though the separate packages still work).\n\n3. **Breaking changes in MSTest v3** include some deprecated APIs being removed and behavioral changes. The main blocker here is that two of the three target frameworks—`net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`—are no longer supported by MSTest v3, so I'd need to understand whether upgrading those frameworks is an option or if they need to stay on MSTest v2.","outputTokens":610,"requestId":"7036:1A47AE:3D4127:47CCEF:69F2BF9E"},"id":"1b852a64-1d68-408b-ad4c-95fbfd5a79e9","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:34:19.563Z","parentId":"20a36510-1304-4604-b1fb-e46ed5272935"}
